        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>An engagement ring is not just an accessory, but a symbol of love, commitment and a story you wouldn’t tire talking about even after decades of receiving this proposal ring. It becomes a part of you, like second skin. It silently sits on your finger and reflects light as you move through your everyday habits for a lifetime. Like any fine jewelry, your engagement ring requires care to sparkle for a lifetime. A little care can go a long way and be the reason why it can become an heirloom piece. To protect a diamond ring’s brilliance and to preserve the thoughtful artistry behind a ring, we have curated this blog to cover everything you need to ensure your ring’s shimmer never fades and the ring stays immaculate for decades!<br/><br/></p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qVyerJ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Proper Ring Care Matters ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Proper Ring Care Matters </h2><p>Most people assume that once the perfect diamond ring is worn, it is safe indefinitely, especially if you have a sedentary lifestyle with little activity. However, daily wear exposes a diamond proposal ring to various elements that can fade the look or lose the diamond. From lotions to accidental knocks that loosen prongs, to the invisible layers of dust and oil that settle on the ring, there are several reasons why your engagement ring’s brilliance dims. </p><p>Proper ring care matters because it helps you not only to preserve the brilliance, but to protect the setting that holds the diamond, while also preserving the ring’s value. To prevent wear and tear that is irreversible, it is important to follow some maintenance habits which are easy while helping you sustain your diamond ring design over a long period of time. </p>",
            "custom_id": "cut"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_A8fUE6": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Daily Habits To Protect Your Engagement Ring ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Daily Habits To Protect Your Engagement Ring </h2><p>Engagement ring care does not have to be complicated. It is easy and with just a few daily habits, you can ensure that your engagement ring stays with you forever without changing. </p>",
            "custom_id": "color"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QG3YBN": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Remove it during certain activities ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Remove it during certain activities </h3>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_ry4cQt": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your ring should not be worn during certain activities that are bound to harm the ring’s brilliance or diamond. Any activity that involves high pressure, chemicals or impact that can knock off the diamond, can lead to damage. Some of the activities include swimming, gym, sports, yoga, weight lifting, gardening and even cooking, especially during kneading and marinating food. Some home cleaners have harsh chemicals that can dull the shine of rings as well. Some ring settings leave the diamond exposed and even a small accidental knock can loosen the stone or bend the prong. Removing your exquisite diamond rings that mean so much to you can help preserve the ring’s shine and save you from unnecessary risks. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Avoid touching the diamond too often",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Avoid touching the diamond too often</h3>",
            "custom_id": "clarity"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_BiE3eV": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We often have the habit to fidget with our unique diamond engagement rings while thinking too hard or when we are emotionally anxious or missing our soulmate. It is tempting to admire the ring and touch it, but our natural oils from our fingertips can add a layer which can also dull the diamond’s shine. This same layer can attract dust, furthering the fadeness.   </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_mEE3FU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Keep it away from lotions and perfumes ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Keep it away from lotions and perfumes </h3>",
            "custom_id": "carat"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_XgNzg9": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with Text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/carat.jpg",
            "text": "<p>Skincare and beauty products leave residue on the edges of the ring and cloud the diamond, slowly affecting the ring. While the impact may not be visible soon, in the long run, the beauty of the diamond fades because of these lotions and perfumes. This is why we recommend the ‘last on, first off’ rule, which essentially suggests that you put on the ring at the last after getting entirely ready and take it off before you get ready for bed. A few seconds of this care and maintenance can ensure that your diamond keeps shining like its new! </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Conclusion",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Lab Grown Diamonds have opened a world of possibilities, offering the same brilliance, strength and beauty as mined diamonds but at a far more accessible price. Grown under conditions that replicate the earth’s natural processes, they share the exact same physical and chemical properties as their mined counterparts, differing only in their origin.</p><p>Like Mined Diamonds, <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry's</a> Lab Grown Diamonds are graded by the 4Cs, giving you a trusted framework to understand a diamond's qualities. However, the 4Cs are simply a guide, not a rulebook. No two diamonds are alike, true beauty lies in what you personally connect with and that’s what makes it truly special.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        }
      },
